messages.message:
Update so far: this concerned doc has 2mil tokens and is timing out while adding to weaviate. The text extracted seems to be in a weird state which @Gaurav Saini is helping us to investigate.
cc: @vineeth @Rakesh
Looks like the cmap for this font is not included in the pdf. The only workaround would be to detect if majority of text contains `cids` and then force image OCR it.

@Gaurav Saini
Yes we will probably need this fallback as well here. Lets chat about this one. Created a JIRA for now for tracking

Lots of different things being tracked in this thread, but I've been looking into the original bug, FLOW-6257/DR-1981. The problem is NASDAQ_KELYA_2020. It says it's being digitized correctly according to the digitization status endpoint, and it even comes back in the tree we get from the documents endpoint - but it doesn't have an ibdoc_path like the other documents. Thus when we classify it and try to look up the name of the document, we can't find it in the tree and get the javascript error.

I'm going to start catching this error in the frontend so it doesn't break everything, but it seems the underlying problem is something in the indexing.
